<h2 style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Ten Frame</h2>

<div style="line-height:2">
<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Ten Frame is a visual tool to helps children build up their number sense. Ten Frame will help children to subitize a number easier and get familiar with numbers that can make 10, numbers within 10 understand the concept of addition and subtraction.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Drag the counters on the Ten Frame to show the value of a number. Use two different colours of counters to show the quantity of each set when we put together or add and use one colour for subtraction. Use the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_pencil.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button to cross out the counters to represent taking away.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Click the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_plus.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button to get the Double Ten Frame on screen. By using the Double Ten Frame, children can extend their learning on numbers up to 20. The Ten Frame and Double Ten Frame can also be use vertically or horizontally. Click the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_rotate_frame.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button to change the orientation of the Ten Frame or the Double Ten Frame.</p>

<p style="font-family:verdana; color:#333">Use the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_eraser.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> or <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_clear.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button to remove all the scribbles with the pencil tool. To start counting a new set of numbers, click the <img src="https://alfaandfriends.com/maths-digitaltools/00-icons/ui_reset.png" width="40" height="40" style="vertical-align:middle"> button.</p>
</div>